benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/children - List children accounts

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval with default and various query parameters (TC01-TC06, TC20).
Empty Response: Scenarios cover no-children (TC07) and all-children-deleted (TC24).
Query Parameters: Multiple combinations tested (TC01-TC06, TC13, TC16, TC19, TC20).
Authorization: Tests cover unauthorized (TC11) and forbidden (TC12) scenarios.
Error Handling: Covers 400 for invalid input (TC09, TC16, TC17), 404 for not found (TC08, TC10, TC25), 503 for service unavailable (TC14), and 504 timeout (TC18).
Edge Cases: Injection attempt (TC17) and unexpected query parameters (TC13) are handled gracefully.
Performance/Volume: Large data volume test (TC15) and concurrent access (TC21) address performance and concurrency concerns.
Audit and Data Consistency: Audit behavior (TC04-TC06, TC22) and data consistency after changes (TC23).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination controls (e.g., page size, page token, and navigating through pages) are present.
Rate Limiting: No tests to verify throttling or rate-limiting behavior under bursty access.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation semantics.
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests to confirm correct behavior with large result sets and proper pagination metadata.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure the system enforces quotas and handles bursts gracefully.
Add tests for caching semantics, including ETag/Cache-Control headers and cache invalidation on data changes.
